Common Lease Expiry Date (CLED)

Common Lease Expiry Date is a key strategic planning tool to better manage the varying lease expiry dates of the land plots in JTC industrial estates. It is only an internal planning date (not publicly announced) to co-terminate new allocations and lease renewals, to recover large contiguous parcels of land, in a cost-efficient manner by managing and administering a common lease expiry date for lands.
Unique Identifier of Carpark

Current Gross floor area (GFA) of product. May differ from Original GFA of product.

GFA consists of all covered floor areas of a building, except otherwise exempted, and uncovered areas for commercial uses for purposes of plot ratio control and development charge. The gross floor area is the total area of the covered floor space measured betwen the centre line of party walls, including the thickness of external walls but excluding voids. Accessibility and usability are not criteria for exclusion from GFA.

Earliest Date where the building received its Temporary Occupancy Permit (TOP)

TOP is the permit granted by the Building Control Division to occupy a new building for a temporary purpose, pending the issuance of Certificate of Statutory Completion. The Building Agreement signed between JTC and its customer stipulates that a customer cannot occupy the factory he has built until the TOP is obtained.
